<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n40079c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40079c">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40079c"> 79(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> my equal</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[T]</font>he &ldquo;patriarchal household&rdquo; is mostly confined to the grandee and the richard, whilst Holy Law and public opinion, neither of which can openly be disregarded, assign command of the household to the equal or first wife and jealously guard the rights and privileges of the others. <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE2"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 198</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: The qualifier &ldquo;my&rdquo; is Joyce&apos;s addition. It suggests that Joyce had in mind a &ldquo;first wife,&rdquo; Nora Barnacle or ALP, at the time he took down the note. [Aida Yared.] <br>Cf. <cite>FW</cite> 141.4 and 141.7. </mm> </dd></dl>
